description: Swinney was the only nominee after he persuaded former Finance Secretary Kate Forbes to join his team rather than challenge him, in a move billed a 'stitch-up' by opponents.
title: John Swinney grabs the poisoned chalice as the former SNP leader is crowned amid warnings over Nationalist 'stitch-up'

description: James Haviland, 63, from Basingstoke tracked down the star as part of a terrifying campaign against her which included staying at her home in Padstow, Cornwall.
title: Fern Britton stalker drove 200 miles to stay in her holiday cottage in her village in 'disturbing and scary' campaign before she called police

description: The number of new mainstream models that are manuals has more than halved in six years, with Volvo, Mercedes-Benz, Jaguar and Lexus no longer offering showroom models.
title: Manual cars may be near extinction in five years as the number of new models halves

description: Birmingham, Manchester and north London are among 15 areas where the long-term ill will received tailored support to rejoin the workforce and prevent a 'spiral of sickness' blighting Britain.
title: Ministers roll out a £64 million plan to help long-term sick back to work and prevent a 'spiral of sickness' blighting Britain
